message.content:
cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with vehicular clouds and communication between vehicles. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses offloading computation-intensive tasks among a collection of vehicles. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper formulates the problem of graph job allocation as a nonlinear integer programming problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper aims to minimize job completion time and data exchange cost, which can be seen as control objectives. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper deals with computation-intensive graph jobs and proposes a framework for efficient allocation of computational resources.
